metadata.name: OK2BBLK
metadata.description:
This powerful street art captures a crucial message of self-acceptance and empowerment.
This photo is a reminder that it is important to embrace and celebrate our differences, and that it is always important to express exactly who we are and to express ourselves honestly and authentically.
The stenciled words are set against the vibrant backdrop of the Lower East Side, New York City.
This limited edition photograph is a powerful reminder to celebrate our diversity and to not apologize for our differences.
The image detail of the two grey sneakers adds a poignant touch, as if the words are being spoken directly to the viewer.
It’s giving: it’s ok to be exactly who you are.
Aina Moyé is recognized as a street photographer and multidisciplinary creative who focuses on mindfulness and the passage of time through the lens of everyday life in neighborhoods in major cities.
Aina is known for her focus on zen practices, mindfulness, and the ever-evolving nature of major city neighborhoods.
